    "result": "Prism PHP is a static analysis tool for PHP applications that helps developers identify potential security vulnerabilities, code quality issues, and bugs in their codebase. It performs deep analysis of PHP code to detect problems like SQL injection vulnerabilities, cross-site scripting (XSS) flaws, authentication bypasses, and other security concerns. The tool integrates with development workflows and CI/CD pipelines to provide automated code scanning. Prism PHP offers detailed reports with remediation guidance and supports various PHP frameworks. It's designed to help development teams maintain secure, high-quality PHP applications by catching issues early in the development process before they reach production."
